Scaling Intelligence Doctrine

The Operating System is founded on the following doctrines.

1. Scaling is Co-Designed, Not Delivered
2. Co-Design Rather than Evaluation
3. Questions Before Answers
4. Evidence Before Opinion
5. Multiple Working Hypotheses
6. Dialogue Before Decision
7. Human Judgement Remains Final
8. Learning Rather than Certainty
9. The Operating System Learns Through Calibration